text:
Sparks flew between Jersey Shore's Ronnie Magro-Ortiz and Malika Haqq as the pair smooched on Sunday's season premiere of Famously Single.

Despite Malika insisting they should just be friends because of their incompatible star signs the pair ended the premiere kissing on the couch as Ronnie told the cameras of their 'natural' connection.

And they were not the only people hooking up in the show's loft as British model David McIntosh and Tiffany Pollard disappeared into a bathroom together before spending the night in bed with each other.

Reality star: Malika Haqq wasted no time pairing up with Jersey Shore star Ronnie Magro-Ortiz during Sunday's season premiere of Famously Single

The first participant to arrive at the loft was Karina Smirnoff of Dancing With The Stars, who told the cameras that she has been engaged three times before, including to Maksim Chmerkovskiy.

'Being engaged a few times and publicly does not really help my reputation but you live and learn,' she told the cameras.

'I think I fall in love way too fast and fall in love with the idea faster than the reality of the situation.

'I think the reason that I am single is that I have a fear of commitment.

Making out: The Dash Dolls star and Jersey Shore store kissed during the season premiere

Getting intimate: Ronnie and Malika rolled around in bed together

Reality stars: The reality stars hit it off instantly on the E! network show

'Getting married is a big deal and everybody goes through their fair share of disaster dates, that's why you have to kiss a lot of frogs.'

Next into the loft was Chad Johnson who gained a bad boy reputation on The Bachelorette and Bachelor In Paradise.

'Bad guys do have more fun but that's also the reason I am single,' said Chad as he told Karina that he was known for getting kicked off reality TV shows.

Fear of commitment: Karina Smirnoff of Dancing With The Stars blamed a fear of commitment for being single

Bad boy: Chad Johnson from The Bachelorette and Bachelor In Paradise also was seeking relationship help

Dorothy Wang was next in and told the cameras that despite growing up wealthy she was a 'real person.'

Wang then said she did not date short or 'dumb' guys or smokers among a long list of deal breakers.

'I just think I have not met the right person yet he must be out there somewhere right? I just don't know where he is,' she said.

Real person: Dorothy Wang insisted that despite her massive family wealth that she was still a 'real person'

Jersey Shore's Ronnie told the cameras he was single after splitting with co-star Sammi 'Sweetheart' Giancola.

'I lose interest, it is like I am all in then I end up doing something stupid and end up back at square one. I think I have commitment fear, that is what drove me away from Sammi,' he said.

TV personality Malika Haqq, Khloe Kardashian's best friend, said she had a reputation for going for unavailable men.

Famous friend: Malika is the best friend of Keeping Up With The Kardashians star Khloe Kardashian

British model David McIntosh told the cameras that he had women throwing themselves at him because of his 'abs and jawline.'

'I do hope to have a family one day but I'm still a bit of a playboy so I gotta figure that out,' he said.

'Can I start being less alpha male type and be loyal? I don't know if I can do that at the moment. The crown weighs heavy on the head.'

British model: David McIntosh was hoping to be less of an alpha male

Tiffany 'New York' Pollard, runner up on Flava Fav's Flavor Of Love, said she wanted to settle down but that it was 'just not happening' for her.

'I know for a fact that I have self sabotaged all of my relationships,' she said.

Next in was Calum Best, who appeared in the first season of the show.

Round tow: Calum Best was back after his disastrous relationship last season with Brandi Glanville

'I am back, bloody hell I must be crazy,' laughed Calum as he said he had learned from the experience and his relationship with Brandi Glanville and wanted to do it differently.

'Here's looking forward to the second time around,' he said.

Dorothy immediately cut herself off from the group and there was immediate tension with a hostile Tiffany.

New surroundings: Dorothy cut herself off from the group

'I know what you are doing, you are trying to make something out of nothing. We are not on your VH1 show,' Dorothy told the cameras.

The group kicked off with the guys and girls pairing off and answering a string of icebreaker questions with coach Robert Mack.

And sparks soon flew between Ronnie and Malika, who both said they wanted the other to hit on them after three drinks.

Face to face: Tiffany got hostile with Dorothy upon first meeting

Second season: The second season of Famously Single airs on the E! network

'I feel like Ronnie's doing the exact same thing he did on Jersey Shore,' Chad told the cameras.

'He literally just walked in the door and was like, ''You, me, relationship now''.'

Calum then said he thought that Karina was the top dating choice, and Chad agreed.

Dating coach: Rob Mack was back to help the celebrities find love

Tiffany told the cameras that she was surprised by Malika's instant attraction to Ronnie.

'I was shocked to see Malika displaying herself like this. Mind you, this is only day one and she's all falling in his lap, rubbing him and whatnot,' she said.

Tiffany said she 'felt honored' as most of the group said she was 'freakiest' in the bedroom.

Teamed up: David and New York also connected quickly

And in a game of' Date, Marry, Dump', both Ronnie and Malika said they would marry each other, although Malika said she was sure she would regret that.

Karina was left fuming when both Calum and Chad said they would dump her and Dorothy said it was understandable that people wanted to marry her.

Calum told the cameras that when he saw the connection between Ronnie and Malika it raised an alarm.

Famous father: Calum is perhaps best known as the son of football legend George Best

'I thought to myself, no dude, it's too early, don't do it, from experience,' he laughed.

And it did not take long for David and New York to get close as she told the cameras she had set her sights on 'man meat.'

'I will screw him until my brain falls out. Oh the things that are swirling through my head,' she said.

She's candid: New York was candid about her intentions with David

David and New York then disappeared into the bathroom and could be heard kissing as Dorothy tried to unpack her bags.

'New York and David are hooking up in the bathroom and it seems like they are getting to know each other better,' said Dorothy.

'David and I went into the bathroom and I felt like when we came out of the bathroom we were a lot closer,' New York admitted.

Bathroom encounter: David and New York were closer after a bathroom encounter

The next morning David admitted it had been 'a heavy night' and that he had ended up in bed with New York.

'I needed David to be my teddy on my first night in a strange house and if he stayed the night with me it would help me get adjusted to the new spot,' she laughed.

Relationship expert Darcy Sterling then told the group she wanted to hear what each of their greatest challenges is.

Relationship expert: Darcy Sterling returned to help the celebrities overcome their issues

Dorothy said she found it difficult to meet new people.

'I am a little judgy. I don't enjoy dating to be honest, I avoid going on dates and speaking to anyone for more than two or three minutes,' said Dorothy.

Ronnie said that before becoming famous he had worked hard to meet women but that it had all changed with his reality TV fame.

MTV star: Ronnie stared on the MTV reality show Jersey Shore

New York admitted she got 'really aggressive and bitchy' with men and had 'penis envy' and needed to learn to respect men.

Malika said she was single as she 'did not trust' and was always 'one foot in and one foot out' of her relationships.

David told the group that his story was one of 'self-destruction' and that he had a history of messing things up with one-night stands.

Group session: The season premiere included a group session with the cast

'It makes me sick is that going to be me for the rest of my life?' he said of his cheating.

'I have got an affliction,' he admitted.

Karina said she was always on the road working and that made life difficult for her and that men wanted to 'tame' her and stop her working and to stay at home.

Road warrior: Karina said she's often on the road working

Chad said he had been single for years and had forgotten what it felt like to be in a relationship and that previous ones had pushed him away from his mom.

Calum said he wanted to be in love and have a family but could not even picture what that would be like.

'The quality of women that you deserve Calum is going to run from that temper of yours,' Darcy told him.

Temper issue: Calum was told that his temper problem was an issue

'We have our work cut out for us,' she told the group as she predicted 'heavy lifting' for each of them.

Later Malika asked Dorothy to chose someone she could be interested in.

'Chad and I can talk very easily, but whatever. David is physically beautiful but I am like whatever,' said Dorothy and Malika told her that Chad was the option.

Girl talk: Dorothy and Malika talked about their options

'He's so dumb,' said Dorothy quietly as Malika covered her mouth as Dorothy admitted that Calum 'was interesting.'

Malika warned her that she needed 'to thaw out a little bit' and not be so cold as she admitted she was surprised to be attracted to Ronnie.

'Malika and Ronnie are kind of hitting it off and honestly it is a little bit surprising to me as I never thought that Malika would be interested in someone from the Jersey Shore,' admitted Dorothy.

Surprise attraction: Malika admitted that she was surprised by her attraction to Ronnie

Total shock: Dorothy was shocked that Malika would go for a Jersey Shore star

Later Malika, a Pisces, and Ronnie, a Sagittarius, realized their star signs were not compatible.

'No wonder I hate-love you. We should just decide to be friends,' said Malika.

Later the pair sat on the couch and Malika told Ronnie she had not expected to like anyone 'and you're the biggest d***' before they began kissing.

'It's natural and just happening and we were making out on the couch,' said Ronnie.

Famously Single returns next week on the E! network.

Cute couple: Ronnie and Malika showed undeniable chemistry
